PART 11 : CONVERSATION HISTORY
Step 1 – Project Introduction
Discussed: The project goal: detect fraud using gyroscope and accelerometer data on a payment interface. Baseline OCSVM accuracy 69%, aim 90%. 441 features, classes “genuine” and “fraud”. Training on genuine only.

Data described: per‑user sessions (40 train, ~35 genuine test, ~25 impostor test), 17 users, each model per user.

Current manual feature selection: using a drop_cols array and trial‑and‑error to test subsets.

First action: Proposed systematic feature selection pipeline (Phase 1–5) based on cleansing, independent rankings, consensus, and OCSVM tuning.

Step 2 – Detailed Data and Model Clarification
Confirmed label encoding (0=genuine, 1=impostor), scaling (StandardScaler), and that OCSVM hyperparameters were fixed (nu=0.05, gamma=0.00055, threshold=0).

Noted that the code for feature generation exists (SessionLevelFeatureExtractor with many defs).

Key problem: Team lead’s hand‑picked set of ~100 features gave TAR ~75% but adding the top‑ranked consensus feature reduced TAR.

Decision: Design a method to evaluate any feature set fairly with automatic hyperparameter tuning.

Step 3 – Feature List Provided
Full list of ~158 features (many concatenated names) was shared.

Clarified that drop_cols array selects features by commenting/uncommenting.

Step 4 – Hyperparameter Tuning Strategy
Proposed LOUO (Leave‑One‑User‑Out) tuning with grid search over nu, gamma (adaptive + fixed 0.00055), threshold, using only 13 dev users.

Emphasised avoiding global tuning that overfits to test set.

Step 5 – Phase 1–5 Full Plan
Outlined Phase 1: data cleansing (drop duplicates, missing, low‑variance, high‑correlation, median imputation).

Phase 2A: Boruta + SHAP (multi:softprob, subsample, colsample_bytree).

Phase 2B: Fisher score with full visualisation.

Phase 2C: RF LOUO with class balancing and 300 trees, saving per‑fold importance.

Phase 3: weighted percentile consensus (50% Boruta, 35% RF, 15% Fisher), fill missing with 0.5.

Phase 5: K‑selection with default OCSVM (nu=0.1, gamma=1/K, threshold=0) – later recognised as insufficient without full tuning.

Step 6 – Implementation of Phase Scripts
Provided complete code for Phase 1 (with median imputation, Spearman correlation, saving removal logs).

Provided Phase 2A (Boruta+SHAP) and Phase 2B (Fisher) scripts.

Discussed issues: missing cleaned features filter in Phase 2C, need for proper gamma candidates, global tuning danger.

Step 7 – Per‑Axis FFT Feature Expansion
Added per‑axis FFT extraction (acc_x, acc_y, acc_z, gyro_x, gyro_y, gyro_z) to extract_fft_features.

Initially saw no TAR gain because the features weren’t called (later corrected).

Step 8 – MFCC and Multitaper Implementation
Added _extract_mfcc_features and _extract_multitaper_features methods.

Critical error: Methods were defined but never called inside extract_fft_features.

After fixing the calls and regenerating CSVs, and combining with tuned hyperparameters, TAR improved.

Step 9 – Global vs LOUO Tuning Scripts
Provided tune_global.py (quick but overfits) and tune_louo.py (honest).

Noted that with only 3 users, LOUO is noisy but still better than global.

Step 10 – Hardcoded Threshold Fix
Discovered that evaluate() in train_session.py used scores >= 0 regardless of the tuned threshold.

After changing to threshold = -0.3, TAR increased noticeably.

Step 11 – Gamma Candidate Error
In tune_global.py, gamma candidates were computed incorrectly as FIXED_GAMMA * mult / n_features instead of mult / n_features, causing extremely small values. Fixed.

Step 12 – Integration of New Features into extract_fft_features
Updated extract_fft_features to call MFCC and Multitaper for magnitude and each axis.

Fixed _fft_defaults to accept prefix and return proper keys for all signals.

Step 13 – Swipe Geometry Feature Addition
Added _extract_swipe_geometry method and integrated into extract_touch_features.

Updated default keys to include swipe_angle_mean, etc.

Step 14 – Expanded LOUO Tuning for 10 Users with FRR Limit
Provided tune_louo_expanded.py with wide hyperparameter grid, FAR ≤ 0.5%, FRR ≤ 30%, using features/v2/ path.

Ready to run on the current 10‑user dataset.

Step 15 – Overfitting Check via Validation Split
Added validate() method to SessionOCSVM (not yet integrated into main loop) to check overfitting using a hold‑out of genuine sessions.

Step 16 – Review of Remaining Feature Enhancements
